        <h3 style="margin-top: 0px;" id="pop_facts">
            Radcliff Population Facts
        </h3>
    


            <h4>What is the current population of Radcliff?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Radcliff is 22,942.  Radcliff, Kentucky is the 1,680th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            
                <h4>What county is Radcliff, Kentucky in?</h4>
                <p>
                
                    Radcliff is located entirely in 
                    Hardin County.
                
                </p>
            

            
                
                    <h4>What is the size of Radcliff, Kentucky in square miles?</h4>
                    Radcliff has an area of 
                    12.4 square miles.

                    
                    
                
            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Radcliff?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Radcliff was in
                    2020, when its population was
                    22,953.
                    
                        In 2020, Radcliff was the
                        1,678th largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 1,680th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Radcliff is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            0.0%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 2020.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Radcliff growing?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Radcliff has grown
                        3.8% 
                        since the 2000.
                    


                    
                        Radcliff, Kentucky's growth is below average.
                        66% of similarly sized
                        cities are growing faster since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            
                <h4>What is the population density of Radcliff, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                Radcliff has a population density of
                1,750.9 people
                per square mile.

                
                
                </p>
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
