        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="demographics">
            Radcliff Demographics
        </h3>
    


            
                

                
                <h4>What is the voting age population of Radcliff, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Radcliff, Kentucky, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 16,746.  The voting age population is 45.9% male and 54.1% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Radcliff, Kentucky residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 13.0% of
                        the residents of Radcliff are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Radcliff, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Radcliff are 58.3% White, 29.6% Black, 6.1% Two or more races, 3.0% Asian, 2.5% Other, 0.3% American Indian and 0.3% Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander. Additionally, 8.1% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Radcliff, Kentucky residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Radcliff, 20.6% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 30.9%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    15.1% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Radcliff.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Radcliff, Kentucky residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 62.6% of
                    Radcliff residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Radcliff, Kentucky residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    89.1% of
                    Radcliff residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 17.5%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 6.6%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Radcliff, Kentucky residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Radcliff residents aged 5 and older, 10.6% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                5.5% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                2.1% speak an Indo-European language, and
                2.9% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="labor">
            Radcliff Income &amp; Labor Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Radcliff, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Radcliff is 9.0%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Radcliff, Kentucky residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Radcliff, 21.8% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Radcliff, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>The median household income in Radcliff is $46,105.</p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="housing">
            Radcliff Housing &amp; Rent Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are owner-occupied in Radcliff, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Radcliff, 50.5% of housing units
                    are occupied by their owners.
                </p>
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are rented in Radcliff, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    Renters occupy 49.5% of housing units in
                    Radcliff.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Radcliff, Kentucky housing units were built before 1940?</h4>
                    <p>
                        Of all the housing units in Radcliff,
                        0.6% of them were build before 1940.
                    </p>
                

                
                

                
                    <h4>What percentage of Radcliff, Kentucky housing units were built after 2000?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Radcliff, 17.9% of the 
                    total housing units were built
                    
                        after the year 2000, which is approximately 
                        
                            1,900 units.
                        
                    
                    </p>
                
                
                
                
